# Backend Architecture Rules

## 1. Layering Rules (Strict)

The backend must follow this structure:

Routes (HTTP layer)
    ↓
Orchestrator (Intent → Command dispatcher)
    ↓
Services (Business logic only)
    ↓
Prisma / External services

Rules:

- Routes MUST NOT contain business logic.
- Routes MUST NOT directly call Prisma (except auth/account loading if explicitly allowed).
- Routes MUST only:
  - Validate input (Zod)
  - Read req.user
  - Call orchestrator
  - Map CommandResult → HTTP response

- Orchestrator MUST:
  - Decide which service method to call based on intent
  - Normalize service errors into CommandError
  - Return CommandResult
  - NOT contain business logic

- Services MUST:
  - Contain all business logic
  - Be independent of Express (no req, res)
  - Throw typed errors (not send responses)
  - Use Prisma
  - Use notification/subscription services

- Services MUST be unit-testable without Express.

---

## 2. Response Contract Stability

API response shapes must remain backward compatible.

CommandResult must preserve existing frontend contract:

Success shapes:
- { success: true, class }
- { success: true, cancelled }
- { success: true, student }
- { success: true, remindersSent }

Error shapes must preserve:
- error (string code)
- message (optional)
- confirmationIssue (optional)
- limit (optional)
- count (optional)

Status codes must not change without explicit approval.

---

## 3. Error Handling Rules

Business logic MUST throw typed errors:
- BASIC_LIMIT_REACHED
- MULTIPLE_CLASSES
- NO_MATCHING_CLASS
- STUDENT_NAME_REQUIRED
- REMINDER_NOT_ALLOWED
- UNSUPPORTED_INTENT

Only orchestrator maps errors to HTTP status codes.

Routes MUST NOT inspect business conditions.

---

## 4. Prisma Usage Rules

- Prisma access allowed ONLY inside:
  - Services
  - Orchestrator (account loading only)

- No Prisma inside:
  - Routes
  - Controllers
  - Middleware (except auth)

---

## 5. Intent Handling Rules

- Intent extraction route (`/api/intent/extract`) must remain independent.
- Orchestrator handles execution only.
- Do not merge extraction + execution without explicit approval.

---

## 6. Adding New Intents

When adding a new intent:

1. Add service method in classService
2. Add mapping in orchestrator
3. Add error handling in mapCommandResultToHttp
4. Update SupportedIntent type
5. Maintain backward compatibility

Never add intent logic directly in routes.

---

## 7. No Silent Contract Changes

Any of the following requires explicit approval:
- Changing response field names
- Changing status codes
- Changing error codes
- Changing Prisma schema
- Moving business logic back into routes